revision.text:
{{ingredient}}

'''Pectin''' is a substance commonly used to thicken foods, mainly liquids. It can be made from [[Cookbook:Apple|apples]].

[[Cookbook:Jam|Jam]]s, [[cookbook:jelly|jellies]], and [[cookbook:preserves|preserves]] will not set unless they have enough pectin in them, so it is often added as an extra ingredient in the form of products such as 'jamsetta'. It is often used as a replacement for [[cookbook:gelatin|gelatin]] in [[Cookbook:vegetarian|vegetarian]] cuisine, alongside [[cookbook:carrageenan|carrageenan]].

