At Wikibooks, '''stubs''' are short, apparently incomplete [[WB:MODULE|module]]s.

Typically, a stub appears because someone creates a new chapter or module of a book which is missing most of the intended content. Stubs tend to contain only a brief description or a suggestion of what the content should be. An incomplete table of contents is also a stub. (If the module only contains nonsense, then it can be [[Wikibooks:Deletion policy|marked for speedy deletion]].)

